title: Cannot configure OneDrive via wizard: error returned immediately when opening auth url using Firefox

milestone.title: v1.58
milestone.description:
Due date shifted 16.01.2022 -> 28.02.2022 by @ivandeex on 13.01.2022
cc @ncw

#### What is the problem you are having with rclone?

Cannot create a new `onedrive` remote using the wizard. The program exits immediately after visiting the proposed url.


#### What is your rclone version (output from `rclone version`)

```
rclone v1.57.0
- os/version: darwin 11.6 (64 bit)
- os/kernel: 20.6.0 (x86_64)
- os/type: darwin
- os/arch: amd64
- go/version: go1.17.2
- go/linking: dynamic
- go/tags: none
```


#### Which OS you are using and how many bits (e.g. Windows 7, 64 bit)

* Darwin sakura.local 20.6.0 Darwin Kernel Version 20.6.0 RELEASE_X86_64 x86_64
* Linux 5.4.0-80-genericx86_64 x86_64 x86_64 GNU/Linux

#### Which cloud storage system are you using? (e.g. Google Drive)

OneDrive

#### The command you were trying to run (e.g. `rclone copy /tmp remote:tmp`)

rclone config

#### A log from the command with the `-vv` flag (e.g. output from `rclone -vv copy /tmp remote:tmp`)

The problem is probably raised by Firefox only, because it tries to fetch `robots.txt` for the local auth url:
```
2021/11/24 10:05:56 DEBUG : Received GET request on auth server to "/robots.txt"
```
The authorization can be successfully completed by using Chrome.
